ately lead to the U.S. Civil War. Taking a truly Atlantic perspective, Marques outlines the multiple forms of U.S. involvement in this traffic amid various legislation and shifting international relations, exploring the global processes that shaped the history of this participation.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aSlave tradezAtlantic Ocean RegionxHistory. 0aSlave tradezUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / Revolutionary Period (1775-1800).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224733423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300224733.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles